We need to create path in worker node eg:path: /mnt/nginx-data
Then we need to create PV

## Step 1 — Persistent Volume (PV)

apiVersion: v1
kind: PersistentVolume
metadata:
  name: nginx-pv
spec:
  capacity:
    storage: 1Gi
  persistentVolumeReclaimPolicy: Retain
  hostPath:
    path: /mnt/nginx-data

## Step 2 — Persistent Volume Claim (PVC)

apiVersion: v1
kind: PersistentVolumeClaim
metadata:
  name: nginx-pvc
spec:
  resources:
    requests:
      storage: 1Gi

## 🎯 Step 3 — Modify Your Deployment to Use PVC

apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: nginx-deployment
spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: nginx
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: nginx
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: nginx
        image: nginx:1.28
        ports:
        - containerPort: 80
        volumeMounts:
        - name: nginx-storage
          mountPath: /usr/share/nginx/html
      volumes:
      - name: nginx-storage
        persistentVolumeClaim:
          claimName: nginx-pvc

Complete Flow (Very Important)
Deployment → Pod → Volume (hostPath) → Node Local Disk (/mnt/data or any path)


If you use type as DirectoryOrCreate in deployment/pod.yaml
NOT need PV or PVC for this configuration.

apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: nginx-hostpath
spec:
  replicas: 1
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: nginx
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: nginx
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: nginx
        image: nginx
        volumeMounts:
        - name: storage
          mountPath: /data

      volumes:
      - name: storage
        hostPath:
          path: /mnt/data
          type: DirectoryOrCreate

